<p><p>Cowleyfornia Studios, developer of Sarawak have recently announced their next story-based adventure game with We'll always have Paris. This will be an emotional one about loving someone with dementia. Much like the previous game, it will support Linux as the engine was developed on Linux.</p>

<p>"This is the story of Simon Smith, a retired chef who lives with Claire, his wife of fifty years. Claire is slowly losing her memory, and Simon must balance his love for her with his desire to maintain normality and autonomy over the confusion that is infiltrating both their lives."</p>

<p>The developer mention that although it is based on their previous game's engine and style "We'll always have Paris is a more experimental narrative experience"</p>

<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hWoZPi9iaZU" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/hWoZPi9iaZU/0.jpg" alt="youtube video thumbnail"><br />Watch video on YouTube.com</a>

<p>We'll always have Paris is a wholesome point and click adventure that explores the lived experience of memory loss, and the beauty of a love that lasts two lifetimes. Features:</p>

<blockquote>
<ul>
	<li>A powerful and emotional narrative</li>
	<li>Pressure-free interactions and mechanics</li>
	<li>A compact experience perfect for playing through in one sitting</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>

<p>You can follow it on <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1520310/Well_always_have_Paris/" target="_blank">Steam</a> and their <a href="https://cowleyforniastudios.itch.io/" target="_blank">itch.io</a> page. It's due out sometime in the Spring.</p><div id="vRYUGn8w4iU17WC">Article from <a href="https://www.gamingonlinux.com/">GamingOnLinux.com</a> taken from the RSS feed.</div></p>